e in our discretion and such modifications are effective upon being posted on the Site.\u00a0 Users should review this Policy periodically to ensure that they are aware of any changes to it.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Data We Collect<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>General Data: When you visit the site, you can browse without submitting any personal information. We do receive a store of non-personal information based on your visit. This information may be used to assess the Site\u2019s performance and usability.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Data Types and Usage<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Personal Data: Personal information is information that can identify you. It is always your choice, or the person acting on behalf of you to provide the personal information.<\/p>\n<p>In order to receive certain communications from us, including but not limited to our blog updates, we ask that you submit your email address to us. All emails you receive from us include an unsubscribe link by which you can opt-out from receiving future emails.<\/p>\n<p>If you contact us at<span>\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:usa@family-peace.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">usa@family-peace.org<\/a><\/span><span>\u00a0<\/span>you are also providing us with private information such as your name and email address. Any communications and contact information may be saved indefinitely.<\/p>\n<p>If you post comments or submit content like photos and videos on the interactive sections of our site, you are consenting to submit your personal information. If you post content on the public access areas of the site, it is publicly available to anyone who visits that section of the Site. Other users and the general public may share or repost any of the content that you submit on the public areas. Copies could remain even if you delete your version.<\/p>\n<p>Automatically Collected Non-Identifiable Information: Non-identifiable information is information collected through your usage of the site that does not identify you. We may collect non-identifiable information automatically and store it. This information includes but is not limited to the date and time of your access, your IP address, information about the platform you used, your browser, browser, host and the pages you visited and length of time of your visit. We will retain your information as long as legally required or allowed. We may dispose of any information in our discretion without notice, as we do not hold any obligation for retention.<\/p>\n<p>We collect non-identifiable information to use for lawful purposes that include diagnosing problems with our server and other Site administration, collecting broad demographic information, assessing site usability based on user movements, and improving and managing the Site.<\/p>\n<p>We may automatically collect non-identifiable information through mechanisms like, but not limited to, pixels, cookies, and third-party analytics providers.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Other Usage:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>We may disclose your information to affiliate entities or organizations and agents and service providers that provide support for the Site or are working directly with us. Use of information will be subject to this Policy, or as restrictive to this Policy.<\/p>\n<p>We may also disclose your information to third party partners that may include non-profit organizations or organizations whose goals and missions align to those of the Site. In such cases we are not liable for the privacy practices of the third party partners.<\/p>\n<p>We may disclose your information for the following legal reasons \u2013 as required by law, to protect our rights, property or safety, to comply with government regulators, law enforcement authorities in connection with judicial proceedings, court orders, subpoena, or legal process served to us, to respond to a physical threat to you or another person.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Regarding European Economic Area Visitors<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>If you are a visitor from the European Economic Area, and you wish to view, update, delete or transfer your personal information, or if you wish to withdraw consent and\/or otherwise exercise your rights pursuant to the GDPR, please email\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:usa@family-peace.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">usa@family-peace.org<\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>Disclaimers; External Links; Children<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>We take reasonable efforts to keep your information secure and compliant to this Policy. However, we cannot ensure that all of your information will never be disclosed in ways not described in this Policy. No transmission of data over the internet is completely secure.<\/p>\n<p>The Site contains links to other sites. We have no control over, and or not liable or responsible for privacy practices and terms of use of those linked sites.<\/p>\n<p>We do not knowingly market the Site to minors, or collect data from or otherwise target minors.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Industry regulatory disclosure requirements<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Smush Plugin: Smush does not interact with end users on your website. The only input option Smush has is to a newsletter subscription for site admins only. If you would like to notify your users of this in your privacy policy, you can use the information below.<\/p>\n<p>Smush sends images to the WPMU DEV servers to optimize them for web use. This includes the transfer of EXIF data. The EXIF data will either be stripped or returned as it is. It is not stored on the WPMU DEV servers.<\/p>\n<p>Smush uses a third-party email service (Drip) to send informational emails to the site administrator. The administrator\u2019s email address is sent to Drip and a cookie is set by the service. Only administrator information is collected by Drip.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Request Your Personal Information<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You can request a copy of your data, correct any data we have about you, or delete information we have about you by contacting\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:usa@family-peace.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">usa@family-peace.org<\/a><\/p>\n<p>If you have questions about this Policy or other matters that relate to it, please contact\u00a0<a href=\"mailto:usa@family-peace.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">usa@family-peace.org<\/a><\/p>\n<p>[\/et_pb_text][\/et_pb_column][\/et_pb_row][\/et_pb_section]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy (\u201cPolicy\u201d) describes how we collect, use, store, process, and share your information. By accessing, browsing, [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":8,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_et_pb_use_builder":"on","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":""},"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v20.10 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Privacy Policy - Family Peace Association USA<\/title>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/usa.family-peace.org\/privacy-policy\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Privacy Policy - Family Peace Association USA\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy (\u201cPolicy\u201d) describes how we collect, use, store, process, and share your information. By accessing, browsing, [&hellip;]\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/usa.family-peace.org\/privacy-policy\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:site_name\" content=\"Family Peace Association USA\" \/>\n<meta property=\"article:modified_time\" content=\"2019-12-20T20:07:40+00:00\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:card\" content=\"summary_large_image\" \/>\n<meta name=\"twitter:label1\" content=\"Est. reading time\" \/>\n\t<meta name=\"twitter:data1\